01:48:13,609 --> 01:48:18,803
⁴And whither I go ye know, and the way
ye know.

1302
01:48:19,581 --> 01:48:25,150
⁵Thomas saith unto him, Lord, we know not
whither thou goest;

1303
01:48:25,351 --> 01:48:28,586
and how can we know the way?

1304
01:48:28,837 --> 01:48:35,527
⁶Jesus saith unto him, I am the way,
the truth, and the life:

1305
01:48:35,728 --> 01:48:40,081
no man cometh unto the Father, but by me.

1306
01:48:40,282 --> 01:48:45,206
⁷If ye had known me, ye should have known
my Father also:

1307
01:48:45,407 --> 01:48:50,650
and from henceforth ye know him, and have
seen him.

1308
01:48:51,278 --> 01:48:57,413
Shri Mataji: “Have seen Him”: see, this
point they miss!

1309
01:49:01,576 --> 01:49:07,422
Yogi: ⁸Philip saith unto him, Lord, show us
the Father, and it sufficeth us.

1310
01:49:07,623 --> 01:49:11,275
⁹Jesus saith unto him, Have I been so long
with you,

1311
01:49:11,476 --> 01:49:15,398
and yet hast thou not known me, Philip?

1312
01:49:15,599 --> 01:49:18,824
He that hath seen me hath seen the Father;

1313
01:49:19,025 --> 01:49:22,883
and how sayest thou, Show us the Father?

1314
01:49:23,092 --> 01:49:29,279
¹⁰Believest thou not that I am in
the Father, and the Father in me?

1315
01:49:29,480 --> 01:49:33,490
The words that I speak unto you I speak
not of myself:

1316
01:49:33,691 --> 01:49:38,527
but the Father that dwelleth in me,
he doeth the works.

1317
01:49:38,728 --> 01:49:44,084
¹¹Believe me that I am in the Father,
and the Father in me:

1318
01:49:44,285 --> 01:49:49,239
or else believe me for the very
works’ sake.

1319
01:49:49,791 --> 01:49:55,634
¹²Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that
believeth on me,

1320
01:49:55,835 --> 01:50:00,606
the works that I do shall he also do;

1321
01:50:00,807 --> 01:50:06,277
and greater works than these shall he do;
because I go unto my Father.

1322
01:50:06,480 --> 01:50:10,459
¹³And whatsoever ye shall ask in my name,
that will I do,

1323
01:50:10,660 --> 01:50:14,376
that the Father may be glorified
in the Son.

1324
01:50:14,577 --> 01:50:21,432
¹⁴If ye shall ask any thing in my name,
I will do it.

1325
01:50:24,756 --> 01:50:28,247
Shri Mataji: Good, beautiful. Come.
Good, now:

1326
01:50:28,448 --> 01:50:33,730
you can take this water in something
else this side. Take it.

1327
01:50:38,558 --> 01:50:43,290
Take the other one now, better…

1328
01:50:46,583 --> 01:50:50,801
Good. Yogi: ¹⁵If ye love me, keep my
commandments.

1329
01:50:51,002 --> 01:50:56,083
Shri Mataji: Loudly. Yogi: ¹⁵If ye love me,
keep my commandments.

1330
01:50:56,298 --> 01:51:01,475
¹⁶And I will pray the Father, and he shall
give you another Comforter,

1331
01:51:01,718 --> 01:51:05,393
that he may abide with you for ever;

1332
01:51:05,594 --> 01:51:09,627
¹⁷Even the Spirit of truth; whom the world
cannot receive,

1333
01:51:09,828 --> 01:51:13,369
because it seeth him not, neither knoweth
him:

1334
01:51:13,570 --> 01:51:20,381
but ye know him; for he dwelleth with you,
and shall be in you.

1335
01:51:20,582 --> 01:51:25,415
¹⁸I will not leave you comfortless: I will
come to you.

1336
01:51:25,615 --> 01:51:29,912
¹⁹Yet a little while, and the world seeth
me no more;

1337
01:51:30,113 --> 01:51:36,370
but ye see me: because I live, ye shall
live also.

1338
01:51:36,570 --> 01:51:41,044
²⁰At that day ye shall know that I am
in my Father,

1339
01:51:41,244 --> 01:51:45,188
and ye in me, and I in you.

1340
01:51:45,389 --> 01:51:49,097
²¹He that hath my commandments, and
keepeth them,

1341
01:51:49,298 --> 01:51:53,858
he it is that loveth me: and he that
loveth me

1342
01:51:54,059 --> 01:51:56,984
shall be loved of my Father and I will
love him …

1343
01:51:57,185 --> 01:52:00,738
Shri Mataji: See now: First Commandment
he said, that you love each other.

1344
01:52:00,939 --> 01:52:04,239
The disciples must love each other, he
didn’t say any Dick, Tom and Harry.

1345
01:52:04,440 --> 01:52:07,503
First love the disciples, all of you should
love each other,

1346
01:52:07,704 --> 01:52:10,436
that’s the main thing is. First thing
is that.

1347
01:52:10,637 --> 01:52:16,735
Second is, “My father”. See
the relationship.

1348
01:52:17,871 --> 01:52:23,037
Yogi: … and I will love him, and will
manifest myself to him.

1349
01:52:23,238 --> 01:52:27,697
²²Judas saith unto him, not Iscariot, Lord,

1350
01:52:27,898 --> 01:52:33,759
how is it that thou wilt manifest thyself
unto us, and not unto the world?

1351
01:52:33,960 --> 01:52:37,657
²³Jesus answered and said unto him,

1352
01:52:37,858 --> 01:52:40,851
If a man love me, he will keep my words:

1353
01:52:41,052 --> 01:52:44,928
and my Father will love him, and we will
come unto him,

1354
01:52:45,128 --> 01:52:48,048
and make our abode with him.

1355
01:52:48,249 --> 01:52:53,140
²⁴He that loveth me not keepeth not
my sayings:

1356
01:52:53,341 --> 01:52:58,512
and the word which ye hear is (not) mine,
but the Father’s which sent me.

1357
01:52:58,713 --> 01:53:03,893
²⁵These things have I spoken unto you,
being yet present with you.

1358
01:53:04,171 --> 01:53:07,651
²⁶But the Comforter, which is the Holy
Ghost,

1359
01:53:07,852 --> 01:53:10,987
 whom the Father will send in my name,

1360
01:53:11,188 --> 01:53:15,761
he shall teach you all things, and bring
all things to your remembrance,

1361
01:53:15,962 --> 01:53:19,456
whatsoever I have said unto you.

1362
01:53:19,657 --> 01:53:24,650
²⁷Peace I leave with you, my peace I give
unto you:

1363
01:53:24,861 --> 01:53:28,529
not as the world giveth, give I unto you.

1364
01:53:28,730 --> 01:53:33,661
Let not your heart be troubled, neither
let it be afraid.

1365
01:53:33,862 --> 01:53:36,981
²⁸Ye have heard how I said unto you,
I go away,

1366
01:53:37,182 --> 01:53:41,980
and come again unto you. If ye loved me,

1367
01:53:42,181 --> 01:53:45,802
ye would rejoice, because I said, I go
unto the Father:

1368
01:53:46,003 --> 01:53:49,593
for my Father is greater than I.

1369
01:53:56,798 --> 01:54:00,010
Shri Mataji: Good. Start it with the high
tones, will keep it up, you see.

1370
01:54:00,210 --> 01:54:02,297
The thing is people must hear you.

1371
01:54:02,497 --> 01:54:06,021
Good. Now just see the hands - vibrations.

1372
01:54:06,222 --> 01:54:10,105
Gavin: And now I have told you before
it come to pass,

1373
01:54:10,322 --> 01:54:14,936
that, when it is come to pass, ye might
believe.

1374
01:54:15,137 --> 01:54:17,527
³⁰Hereafter I will not talk much with you:

1375
01:54:17,728 --> 01:54:23,182
for the prince of this world cometh, and
hath nothing in me.

1376
01:54:23,383 --> 01:54:26,719
³¹But that the world may know that I love
the Father;

1377
01:54:26,920 --> 01:54:31,743
and as the Father gave me commandment,
even so I do.

1378
01:54:31,944 --> 01:54:37,279
Shri Mataji: Hm!
Yogi: Arise, let us go hence.

1379
01:54:39,345 --> 01:54:45,419
¹I am the true vine, and my Father is
the husbandman.

1380
01:54:45,620 --> 01:54:51,357
²Every branch in me that beareth not fruit
he taketh away:

1381
01:54:51,558 --> 01:54:55,219
and every branch that beareth fruit,
he purgeth it…

1382
01:54:55,420 --> 01:54:59,914
Shri Mataji: See!
Gavin: …that it may bring forth more fruit.

1383
01:55:00,939 --> 01:55:05,745
³Now ye are clean through the word which
I have spoken unto you.

1384
01:55:05,946 --> 01:55:11,038
⁴Abide in me, and I in you.

1385
01:55:11,239 --> 01:55:16,503
As the branch cannot bear fruit of itself,
except it abide in the vine;

1386
01:55:16,704 --> 01:55:21,603
no more can ye, except ye abide in me.

1387
01:55:21,819 --> 01:55:25,629
⁵I am the vine, ye are the branches:

1388
01:55:25,830 --> 01:55:28,919
He that abideth in me, and I in him,

1389
01:55:29,120 --> 01:55:32,545
the same bringeth forth much fruit:

1390
01:55:32,746 --> 01:55:36,928
for without me ye can do nothing.

1391
01:55:37,691 --> 01:55:43,099
⁶If a man abide not in me, he is cast forth
as a branch, and is withered;

1392
01:55:43,300 --> 01:55:49,201
and men gather them, and cast them into
the fire, and they are burned.

1393
01:55:49,844 --> 01:55:53,587
⁷If ye abide in me, and my words abide
in you,

1394
01:55:53,788 --> 01:55:58,612
ye shall ask what ye will, and it shall be
done unto you.

1395
01:55:58,813 --> 01:56:03,534
⁸Herein is my Father glorified, that ye
bear much fruit;

1396
01:56:03,735 --> 01:56:07,643
so shall ye be my disciples.

1397
01:56:08,882 --> 01:56:13,586
⁹As the Father hath loved me, so have I
loved you:

1398
01:56:13,787 --> 01:56:17,198
continue ye in my love.

1399
01:56:17,415 --> 01:56:21,777
¹⁰If ye keep my commandments, ye shall
abide in my love;

1400
01:56:21,994 --> 01:56:28,593
even as I have kept my Father’s
commandments, and abide in his love.

1401
01:56:30,833 --> 01:56:32,558
¹¹These things have I spoken unto you,
Shri Mataji: All right. Now come along.

1402
01:56:32,759 --> 01:56:36,323
